This past Friday, a motorcycle rider was lucky to escape with his life after colliding with a motor vehicle on the corner of Ontdekkers Road and Corlett Avenue, reports the Roodepoort Record.The accident occurred at about 5.10pm.According to sources, the motorcycle was travelling on Ontdekkers Road in the direction of Westgate Shopping Centre when the motor vehicle travelling from the opposite direction turned in front of him.The motorcyclist only sustained moderate injuries and was allegedly seen walking around on the accident scene.The accident will be the subject of an investigation by the relative authorities. Caxton News ServiceRead original story on roodepoortrecord.co.za